  "general_provisions": "This bill creates a process to cure an initiative or referendum petition signature that is declared invalid.",
  "hilighted_provisions": "This bill:<hr><ltbullet>establishes a process to cure a signature on an initiative or referendum petition that is declared invalid by a county clerk because the signature does not match the signature on file in the statewide voter registration database;<hr><ltbullet>requires a county clerk to notify an individual described above when the county clerk determines that the individual's signature does not match the signature on file;<hr><ltbullet>allows the individual to cure the invalid signature by delivering to the county clerk a signed affidavit attesting to the validity of the signature;<hr><ltbullet>establishes deadlines related to the processes described above; and<hr><ltbullet>provides that a county clerk may not count the individual's signature as valid unless the affidavit is timely received.",
